# Spec Kit (Spec-Driven Development)

From [github/spec-kit](https://github.com/github/spec-kit). Skills live under `.cursor/skills/speckit-*/`.

## When to use

Use Spec Kit for **greenfield work, net-new features, or multi-phase builds** where requirements should become executable artifacts before code.

Do **not** force Spec Kit for trivial one-line fixes, typo edits, or tasks the user wants implemented immediately with only `planning.mdc` + `ponytail`.

## Prerequisites

Target code project must have a `.specify/` directory (templates + scripts). If missing:

```powershell
# from cursor-config-coding
.\scripts\install-spec-kit.ps1 -Target "D:\path\to\code-repo"
```

Skills expect PowerShell scripts under `.specify/scripts/powershell/` on Windows.

## Workflow (skills)

Run in order. Invoke by skill name or `/speckit-*`:

| Step | Skill | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| 1 | `speckit-constitution` | Project principles / governing guidelines |
| 2 | `speckit-specify` | What & why — requirements / user stories |
| 3 | `speckit-clarify` (optional) | De-risk ambiguities before planning |
| 4 | `speckit-plan` | Tech stack + implementation plan |
| 5 | `speckit-checklist` (optional) | Quality checklist for requirements |
| 6 | `speckit-tasks` | Actionable task breakdown |
| 7 | `speckit-analyze` (optional) | Cross-artifact consistency check |
| 8 | `speckit-implement` | Execute tasks |
| 9 | `speckit-converge` | Assess codebase vs artifacts; append remaining work |
| — | `speckit-taskstoissues` | Convert tasks → GitHub issues |

## Precedence with this config

1. **`ponytail`** still gates every code change (minimal correct diff).
2. Spec Kit owns the **spec → plan → tasks → implement** artifact chain for feature work.
3. Existing `planning.mdc` approval gate still applies before non-trivial coding unless the user said skip plan / just do it.
4. Architecture skills (`frontend-architecture`, etc.) apply when designing within `/speckit-plan` / implement.

